2019-12-16 00:26:24	ramsub071	Morning everyone! I've a dictionary whose keys are range(1,N) and values are strings. I'd like to do a slice operation over this dict, dict1[a:b] how do I go about?
2019-12-16 00:26:32	<--	soniya29 (soniya@nat/redhat/x-fpnnfulpakccyliz) has quit (Ping timeout: 276 seconds)
2019-12-16 00:27:18	Death916	celphi what u mean go to next line
2019-12-16 00:27:31	papna	ramsub071: You could do {k: v for k, v in d.items() if a <= k < b} if you want
2019-12-16 00:27:43	KirkMcDonald	ramsub071: Well, a dict doesn't support slicing.
2019-12-16 00:27:44	papna	ramsub071: It sounds like a list might be better-suited for you than a dict.
2019-12-16 00:27:50	KirkMcDonald	ramsub071: So you'd need a loop.
2019-12-16 00:27:55	energizer	ramsub071: list(sorted(d.items())[a:b]
2019-12-16 00:28:11	energizer	er
2019-12-16 00:28:20	energizer	ramsub071: list(v for k,v in sorted(d.items())[a:b]
2019-12-16 00:28:27	-->	nathias (~nathias@unaffiliated/nathias) has joined #python
2019-12-16 00:28:30	KirkMcDonald	{k: d[k] for k in range(a, b)}
2019-12-16 00:28:34	-->	dmt` (dmt@gateway/shell/xzibition.com/x-qzfmihfbgjloulda) has joined #python
2019-12-16 00:28:44	KirkMcDonald	Possibly with an 'if k in d', if that is needed.
2019-12-16 00:28:54	energizer	ramsub071: what is the output type that youw ant?
2019-12-16 00:29:02	energizer	(that you want
2019-12-16 00:29:10	ramsub071	energizer: perfect that's pretty much it :)
2019-12-16 00:29:40	papna	energizer: a-1:b-1
2019-12-16 00:29:42	ramsub071	KirkMcDonald: papna been a while haven't seen you around here, maybe timezones
2019-12-16 00:30:23	papna	ramsub071: Hope you've been well.
2019-12-16 00:30:45	energizer	KirkMcDonald: that is nice
2019-12-16 00:30:46	<--	YuGiOhJCJ (~YuGiOhJCJ@gateway/tor-sasl/yugiohjcj) has quit (Quit: YuGiOhJCJ)
2019-12-16 00:30:49	<--	mynameisbrian (~brian@2607:fcc8:6a09:300:d884:39b3:512:48a1) has left #python ("Leaving")
2019-12-16 00:31:11	-->	lapoo (~dev4@89-212-52-180.static.t-2.net) has joined #python
2019-12-16 00:31:27	KirkMcDonald	If it's a list that is wanted, [d[k] for k in range(a, b)]
2019-12-16 00:31:48	energizer	ramsub071: ^
