2019-12-16 05:46:54	-->	jokoon (~jokoon@unaffiliated/jokoon) has joined #python
2019-12-16 05:48:05	cdunklau	karstenk: your _monitor_service method calls monitor.connect() and then monitor.listen_thread.start(). if monitor.connect fails during the connect operation, the attribute `listen_thread` never gets assigned
2019-12-16 05:48:51	karstenk	sure
2019-12-16 05:48:57	<--	Rurik (~textual@unaffiliated/temur) has quit (Quit: Rurik)
2019-12-16 05:49:03	cdunklau	karstenk: but it doesn't throw an exception, so _monitor_service continues to monitor.listen_thread.start() which fails because monitor.listen_thread is None, and None doesn't have a start() method
