2019-12-16 16:10:54	Yhg1s	FLHerne: if you use 's*' to get a PyBuffer, the PyBuffer will keep the underlying object alive as long as it's not released.
2019-12-16 16:11:00	Yhg1s	FLHerne: you do need to release it when you're done.
