2019-12-16 23:31:00	Shirakawasuna	Mrbuck, x[x['some']][0] means this: isolate the column called 'some' from DataFrame x. Use it to filter to the rows where the values in 'some' are true-ish. Then get the element at index 0. It's important to understand that index 0 is not necessarily the first row, it is actually a label. You can think of it as an ID for the row.
