2019-12-17 12:04:39	Widdershins	that's the lesson here
2019-12-17 12:04:40	dunpeal	in Python 2, you had str as a default string type, and you were supposed to use it as a character string, even though it was actually a bytes string
2019-12-17 12:05:00	dunpeal	that's the reason Python 3 defaults to a real character string (i.e. str became a character string)
2019-12-17 12:05:16	dunpeal	and bytes was introduced to a be a proper, exclusive bytes string.
2019-12-17 12:05:43	--	jan61 is now known as jan6
2019-12-17 12:05:45	dunpeal	so using bytes as a character string is going back to the kludge it was designed to fix.
