2019-12-17 12:23:38	nanonyme	confluency, maybe, sure. It's just, posixpath exists to give you a guarantee that the separator is a forward slash and some other things
2019-12-17 12:23:40	dunpeal	Python2 str and Python3 bytes are both bytestrings under the hood
2019-12-17 12:23:49	thevishy	ah
2019-12-17 12:24:03	dunpeal	it's just that in Python2 str has a different API and was supposed to be used a character string
2019-12-17 12:24:19	dunpeal	(which is exactly the SNAFU Python 3 has adderessed with its changes)
2019-12-17 12:24:45	Widdershins	basically in the time since python was first conceived, unicode turned out to be pretty important
