2019-12-17 12:25:25	dunpeal	yeah, I'm guessing str and unicode are different because unicode was tacked-on later
2019-12-17 12:25:36	dunpeal	thevishy: s[] is an API
2019-12-17 12:25:54	dunpeal	s[x] calls s.__getitem__(x)
2019-12-17 12:25:58	-->	seni (~Nimitz14@cpc91224-cmbg18-2-0-cust82.5-4.cable.virginm.net) has joined #python
2019-12-17 12:26:06	thevishy	ah okay
2019-12-17 12:26:10	thevishy	i think I get your point
2019-12-17 12:26:27	dunpeal	so if s[x] in Python2 str returns 'c' and in Python3 bytes returns 12, that's an API change.
2019-12-17 12:26:39	-->	thats_al1 (~Conlan@2620:cc:8000:1c85:a109:e9e4:dab5:3e43) has joined #python
